"Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging d313e24f18c2d215e0d878a5db83cd7936182263 with DEVEDITION_68_0b1_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c1c7a9966c5a313a27af9c001882b168bf6142b1", "parents": ["d313e24f18c2d215e0d878a5db83cd7936182263"], "tags": []}], "date": 1557759127, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11268": {"changesets": [{"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551045 - add debug log in `vtt.jsm`. r=heycam\n\nWe should add some debug logs, which should be easily enable and disable, in vtt.jsm in order to increase the efficiency of debugging.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30798", "files": ["dom/media/webvtt/vtt.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c99c6daa9db60f35fb85956271fd855e7c0cd7b", "parents": ["fa3cfee27619ddc9bcbcf70555bda4eb1e815146"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bitbucket@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1252310 - Don't mistakenly suppress key-up event when not required. r=geckoview-reviewers,m_kato\n\nThe problem from bug 1278581 was that hiding the URL bar in response to a\nkey-down event (for the Enter key) would then lead to the corresponding key-up\nevent then ending up in GeckoView, thereby confusing the \"last user activity\"\ntracking.\nIt appears that this only happens with key events received through the\nregular OnKeyListener, but not with events coming from the OnKeyPreImeListener.\n\nOn devices where pressing Enter in the URL bar would transmit the key event\nthrough the latter mechanism, this means that because the key-up event we wanted\nto suppress in BrowserApp never arrived, we would instead suppress whatever\nother key event would arrive next, e.g. possibly a press of the back button.\nThis would lead to the observed behaviour where after entering an URL, the first\nsubsequent press of the back button might then be ignored.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30573", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/toolbar/BrowserToolbar.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/toolbar/ToolbarEditText.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c7feffe40029e833241baa952cec89346d649a06", "parents": ["5c99c6daa9db60f35fb85956271fd855e7c0cd7b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Narcis Beleuzu \u003cnbeleuzu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1546930 - Disable browser_toggleTransparentOverlay-2.js on Linux for frequent failures r=jmaher\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30809", "files": ["toolkit/components/pictureinpicture/tests/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fbc8b6af3e5499c317e3d481f44ca84f77c459a9", "parents": ["c7feffe40029e833241baa952cec89346d649a06"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florin Strugariu \u003cfstrugariu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1549948 Fenix jobs are failing with \"activity class does not exist\" r=rwood\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30359", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/raptor.yml", "testing/mozharness/mozharness/mozilla/testing/raptor.py", "testing/raptor/raptor/cmdline.py", "testing/raptor/raptor/raptor.py", "testing/raptor/test/test_cmdline.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0867f9a289a712042a2d915be5142ae6d9fcd616", "parents": ["fbc8b6af3e5499c317e3d481f44ca84f77c459a9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551065 - Properly discard empty lines for -webkit-line-clamp. r=heycam\n\nThat being said, this code is clearly not getting hit, are we 100% sure that\nthis is interoperable with what WebKit / Blink do?\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30830", "files": ["layout/generic/nsBlockFrame.cpp", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-overflow/webkit-line-clamp-033.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "430b79a1444fd6935ea68abfbdb7a53d8e572b78", "parents": ["0867f9a289a712042a2d915be5142ae6d9fcd616"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1542184 - Use PersistentRooted for rooting vectors of GC things from rust code r=fitzgen?\n\nThis replaces the use of heap-alloced Rooted with PersistentRooted which is safe wrt destruction order.\n\nI had to add PersistentRooted and StackGCVector to OPAQUE_TYPES to make this work... I'm not really sure what this does.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30668", "files": ["js/public/GCVector.h", "js/public/TypeDecls.h", "js/rust/build.rs", "js/rust/src/glue.rs", "js/rust/src/jsglue.cpp", "js/rust/src/rust.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4b8f9814a1ea6f412d1f02c2701096b048cd0707", "parents": ["430b79a1444fd6935ea68abfbdb7a53d8e572b78"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kestrel \u003cke5trel@protonmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551165 - Add context fill to about:performance icons for dark mode r=ntim\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30878", "files": ["toolkit/components/aboutperformance/content/aboutPerformance.xhtml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a0d20ab6be8b779fdd96a14f0cfd07ffe73c8e3d", "parents": ["4b8f9814a1ea6f412d1f02c2701096b048cd0707"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551072 - Need xpcshell check in addition to automation. r=Felipe\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30812", "files": ["toolkit/components/enterprisepolicies/EnterprisePolicies.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7bb36c2fe72cbc073b1fdd64da8bc15ec5ec8d87", "parents": ["a0d20ab6be8b779fdd96a14f0cfd07ffe73c8e3d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551167 - Move import of mochitest/helpers/context.js to test instead of head.js r=pbro\n\nImporting scripts in shared head files is hard to maintain because it forces all browser ini that use the shared file to whitelist all its imports.\nThe debugger context helper is almost unused in the inspector, so it would be easier to just import it in the few tests that require it.\nAlso removed the whitelist entry in rules' browser.ini, no test in this suite used it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30882", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/rules/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/test/browser_inspector_highlighter-07.js", "devtools/client/inspector/test/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "87e01787d465cfcb89c0e593685c15d43a30f61e", "parents": ["7bb36c2fe72cbc073b1fdd64da8bc15ec5ec8d87"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mihai Alexandru Michis \u003cmalexandru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1543316 - Disable multiple-update.https.html on sw-e10s r=jmaher\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30876", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/service-workers/service-worker/multiple-update.https.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "481580bf3fe866774c10b37850c21990096c53e2", "parents": ["87e01787d465cfcb89c0e593685c15d43a30f61e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tooru Fujisawa \u003carai_a@mac.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1549340 - Part 2: Use union instead of reinterpret_cast to initialize const char* with symbol for JSPropertySpec.name. r=jandem\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30493", "files": ["dom/bindings/BindingUtils.cpp", "js/public/PropertySpec.h", "js/public/Sym