d43e1a28888ffffcbdf02131a53 with DEVEDITION_68_0b4_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "88c736be60c502525eafd4feeb6395484e2f7989", "parents": ["23268f044fbead618a2ec7c75ac9073afb71eadd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558627686, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11299": {"changesets": [{"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 1: Factorize android.yml r=tomprince a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29849", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/build/android.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65f7c0babe096a07dc01456c09fad7632888d6f4", "parents": ["88c736be60c502525eafd4feeb6395484e2f7989"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 2: Let should_use_artifact_map() not depend on the project anymore r=tomprince a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31492", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_checksums.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_langpack_checksums.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_repackage.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_source_checksums.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_beetmover_signed_addons.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_generate_checksums_beetmover.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bf2b338d006a89b15dfe76868dc10a29f6e91243", "parents": ["65f7c0babe096a07dc01456c09fad7632888d6f4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 3: Enable `-beta` Android builds r=Callek a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29850", "files": ["mobile/android/config/mozconfigs/android-aarch64/beta-profile-use", "taskcluster/ci/balrog/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/beetmover/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/build/android.yml", "taskcluster/ci/generate-profile/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/instrumented-build/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_candidates_checksums.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_nightly.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_nightly_checksums.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_geckoview.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/builds/releng_sub_android_configs/64_aarch64_beta_pgo.py", "testing/mozharness/mozharness/mozilla/building/buildbase.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f58c24f5f8543fde39d341ac43ed18ea5e87c7f2", "parents": ["bf2b338d006a89b15dfe76868dc10a29f6e91243"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 4: Change promote_fennec to handle beta tasks only r=Callek a=release\n\nThis means `-nightly` tasks don't end up in that promote graph.\nThe push-apk loader also wires the expected dependencies.\nWe also ensure geckoview Nightly is not shipped off mozilla-beta by not exposing the geckoview artifacts on the nightly build tasks\n\nShip Nightly to the alpha track of Google Play\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29851", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/beetmover/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/google-play-strings/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/push-apk-checks/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/push-apk/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/loader/push_apk.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_candidates.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/target_tasks.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_geckoview.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/google_play_strings.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/push_apk.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/push_apk_checks.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_deps.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d51fe28644b8b66c0b7dfc4a0504813aeef52640", "parents": ["f58c24f5f8543fde39d341ac43ed18ea5e87c7f2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 5: Make single locale run on try too r=Callek a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29855", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/nightly-l10n/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "851a7d71d98070ecfdaf4be0b230f979b6d2283b", "parents": ["d51fe28644b8b66c0b7dfc4a0504813aeef52640"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 7: .cron.yml: Let mozilla-beta schedule the Fennec nightly graph r=Callek a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D29857", "files": [".cron.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "52054d2cc61caca3d9e413ac288eddd05de065d7", "parents": ["851a7d71d98070ecfdaf4be0b230f979b6d2283b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 8: Run emulator tests on beta r=jmaher a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31273", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/test-platforms.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aae928d56c33a5e7320716f82f6f56ea7f50ab14", "parents": ["52054d2cc61caca3d9e413ac288eddd05de065d7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 9: Ensure MOZ_UPDATE_CHANNEL is set to either nightly or beta r=tomprince,jmaher\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31274", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/build/android.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/tests.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec804fef742ef89cce39b2443812523f017bdeeb", "parents": ["aae928d56c33a5e7320716f82f6f56ea7f50ab14"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 10: Use release-type attributes r=Callek a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32315", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/build/android.yml", "taskcluster/ci/google-play-strings/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/push-apk-checks/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/push-apk/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-bouncer-aliases/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-bouncer-sub/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-generate-checksums/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-mark-as-shipped/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-notify-promote/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-notify-ship/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-notify-started/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-source/kind.yml", "taskcluster/docs/attributes.rst", "taskcluster/taskgraph/loader/push_apk.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/source_checksums.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/source_files.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/target_tasks.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/per_platform_dummy.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_deps.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/upload_generated_sources.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/upload_symbols.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/attributes.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9196b576f69a07fb670394ce81f3e1f0b5965b9d", "parents": ["ec804fef742ef89cce39b2443812523f017bdeeb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 11: Let Fennec Nightly be signed by the nightly key r=Callek a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31802", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/push_apk.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/signing.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c6efa45fbc6946d76841fdf4c9605e45171e6b3b", "parents": ["9196b576f69a07fb670394ce81f3e1f0b5965b9d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548864 - part 12: Fix beetmover version numbers on Fennec nightly r=Callek a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32137", "files": [".cron.yml", "taskcluster/ci/config.yml", "taskcluster/mach_commands.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/config.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/cron/decision.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/cron/schema.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/decision.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/parameters.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/test/test_decision.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d3935fc2c8ec9982b4154b8df056ffbc58a85cfa", "parents": ["c6efa45fbc6946d76841fdf4c9605e45171e6b3b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 4d774e730d76", "files": ["mobile/android/config/mozconfigs/android-aarch64/nightly", "mobile/android/config/mozconfigs/android-api-16/nightly", "mobile/android/config/mozconfigs/android-x86/nightly", "mobile/android/config/mozconfigs/android-x86_64/nightly"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f2cf02d4beba08f432cb2a6fabb3d20a6a59ba9", "parents": ["d3935fc2c8ec9982b4154b8df056ffbc58a85cfa"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558670812, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "jlorenzo@mozilla.com"}, "11300": {"changesets": [{"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554048 - Fennec Nightly: checksums are uploaded in the candidates directory, instead of the nightly one r=mtabara a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32414", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/beetmover-checksums/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_candidates.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_candidates_checksums.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_nightly.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/manifests/fennec_nightly_checksums.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b7bf7fa2d8c476df3a2462c20259e239ab1770c0", "parents": ["1f2cf02d4beba08f432cb2a6fabb3d20a6a59ba9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554051 - Fennec Nightly: Cannot beetmove to nightly folder: release/candidates scopes are given to the task r=mtabara a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32423", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_checksums.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_langpack_checksums.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_push_to_release.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_repackage.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_repackage_partner.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_source_checksums.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_beetmover_signed_addons.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_generate_checksums_beetmover.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/signing.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f46b19ec841c939b84fa40be8b326a11141e6da", "parents": ["b7bf7fa2d8c476df3a2462c20259e239ab1770c0"], "tags": ["FENNEC_68_0b4_BUILD1"]}], "date": 1558684195, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "jlorenzo@mozilla.com"}, "11301": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 2f46b19ec841c939b84fa40be8b326a11141e6da with FENNEC_68_0b4_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "825151707e44f7258d09b628c5fa71f0168d076d", "parents": ["2f46b19ec841c939b84fa40be8b326a11141e6da"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558693732, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11302": {"changesets": [{"author": "J.C. Jones \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552339 - On Android, direct attestations are anonymized r=keeler a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32057", "files": ["dom/webauthn/tests/test_webauthn_attestation_conveyance.html", "dom/webauthn/tests/u2futil.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f76b9ef5c2e9f48c7838fe075d5509d0474d724a", "parents": ["825151707e44f7258d09b628c5fa71f0168d076d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550523 - Ensure that decoding methods for frozen images request the correct frame. r=tnikkel a=jcristau\n\nWith WebRender, we had observed that the print preview for animated\nimages was not displaying correctly. It should display the first frame\nbut it was showing nothing the first time the preview was opened. Once\nthe decoded image was available in the cache, it would display\ncorrectly if the preview was reloaded.\n\nThe StartDecoding and RequestDecode variants always requested\nFRAME_CURRENT for animated images. They should use FRAME_FIRST for\nstatic requests / FrozenImage. Correcting this fixes the print preview.\n\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32033", "files": ["image/DynamicImage.cpp", "image/FrozenImage.cpp", "image/FrozenImage.h", "image/ImageWrapper.cpp", "image/RasterImage.cpp", "image/RasterImage.h", "image/VectorImage.cpp", "image/imgIContainer.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e3ebfd849558d6011dec7b53ea5942ba1da8867", "parents": ["f76b9ef5c2e9f48c7838fe075d5509d0474d724a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1545842 - Downgrade RestyleManager assertions to DIAGNOSTIC_ASSERT in beta. r=tnikkel a=jcristau\n\nThe only case where we know that this assert breaks right now is in\nnsIconChannel.\n\nnsIconChannel is used for moz-icon://, which is not exposed to content.\n\nSo it doesn't seem to be easy to potentially get into a broken state that\ncontent could exploit, and thus crashes in release may be a bit excessive.\n\nDowngrade the assertion for now.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com//D28248", "files": ["layout/base/RestyleManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5d6b91a3b5365903cd7d2c48bf32f62e50bff46a", "parents": ["3e3ebfd849558d6011dec7b53ea5942ba1da8867"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558696403, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "opoprus@mozilla.com"}, "11303": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552302 - Link policy message to about:policies. r=Gijs a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32061", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/preferences.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0fa8984d53a3c816d6b841d3141cba963c8a99a8", "parents": ["5d6b91a3b5365903cd7d2c48bf32f62e50bff46a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Lemley \u003crob@thunderbird.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552422 - correct Balrog scope for comm-esrXX branches. r=tomprince a=jcristau\n\nCopying fix from THUNDERBIRD_60_VERBRANCH on mozilla-esr60.\nhttps://hg.mozilla.org/releases/mozilla-esr60/rev/eae0435135ad6713bf9d776f71b7d7cc3e01756d\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31584", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37d53d3dcb7d8a38ed853a0222a2a0080f011afc", "parents": ["0fa8984d53a3c816d6b841d3141cba963c8a99a8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530650 - Add --cap-lints warn to RUSTFLAGS when not building with --enable-warnings-as-errors. r=froydnj a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32080", "files": ["build/moz.configure/warnings.configure"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "66dc57c3cf310258fe2d0e8dc31942ded5c91626", "parents": ["37d53d3dcb7d8a38ed853a0222a2a0080f011afc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553226 - Don't attempt to read annotations associated with Flash process crashes r=froydnj a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32133", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/nsExceptionHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "de5bd9e725c461391d517148db35634c990ebe90", "parents": ["66dc57c3cf310258fe2d0e8dc31942ded5c91626"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dzmitry Malyshau \u003cdmalyshau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551520 - Use WR relative transform instead of the world inverse r=gw a=jcristau\n\nThis is a follow-up to https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30600\n\nPreviously, I changed changed the space mapper logic to use the world transformations.\nThis was seemingly needed because we requrested the relation between primitives and\ntheir clip nodes, which could be in unrelated spatial sub-trees.\nHowever, I believe the change was a mistake, since for clips we should not even try\nto get the relative mapping, and clipping is done in world space for these cases.\nThis change reverts that logic back. ~~Fingers crossed for the try to not show any\nasserts firing up inside get_relative_transform.~~ Try is green \ud83c\udf89\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32382", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/clip_scroll_tree.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/display_list_flattener.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/picture.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/prim_store/mod.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "33e1639074404212817de4e245aa1fac0d64d2eb", "parents": ["de5bd9e725c461391d517148db35634c990ebe90"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Boris Zbarsky \u003cbzbarsky@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553286.  Mark legacycall hooks (and a few other binding hooks) as MOZ_CAN_RUN_SCRIPT.  r=mccr8 a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32053", "files": ["dom/bindings/Codegen.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "77f31bca1162ba864c92da3050a6cfa079aaa0d7", "parents": ["33e1639074404212817de4e245aa1fac0d64d2eb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551275 - Refactor jsapi weak map tests r=sfink a=jcristau\n\nThis removes a bunch of repeated code and hopefully makes it easier to see what we're testing.  When marking two things the same color this now checks both orders (e.g. key before map, map before key).  I removed individual test cases and generate all possiblities with for loops.  The expected marking state is determined by functions factored out from the verifier.\n\nThe tests for JS WeakMap and internal weakmaps are slightly different because I wanted to cover all existing test cases without making things too complicated.  This means we don't test marking the key and delegate different colors for the former.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30948", "files": ["js/src/gc/Verifier.cpp", "js/src/gc/Verifier.h", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testGCGrayMarking.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e408eb60134bd6b5a148fa7d2e46076596e9dd94", "parents": ["77f31bca1162ba864c92da3050a6cfa079aaa0d7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1534394 - Make WSRunObject::InsertText() set aPointAfterInsertedString by itself when HTMLEditor::InsertTextWithTransaction() returns error r=m_kato a=jcristau\n\nOddly, `WSRunObject::InsertText()` returns `NS_OK` even when\n`HTMLEditor::InsertTextWithTransaction()` returns error.  However,\nit fails if insertion point is not editable like `\u003cnoscript\u003e` element.\nIn such case, `aPointAfterInsertedString` isn't modified and its caller,\n`HTMLEditRules::WillInsertText()` keep handling inserting remaining text\nwith non-positioned `EditorDOMPoint`.  Therefore, at the next time,\n`WSRunObject` fails to do anything since it requires positioned\n`EditorDOMPoint`.\n\nFor making uplift safer, this patch makes `WSRunObject::InsertText()` set\n`aPointAfterInsertedString` by itself when\n`HTMLEditor::InsertTextWithTransaction()` returns error.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32131", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.cpp", "editor/libeditor/WSRunObject.cpp", "editor/libeditor/crashtests/1534394.html", "editor/libeditor/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "54ff09f869d8e81bda1bf1c76816e8c6792ccf66", "parents": ["e408eb60134bd6b5a148fa7d2e46076596e9dd94"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jason Laster \u003cjlaster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552987 - Jump-to-function-definition buttons are no longer visible in the console. r=nchevobbe a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32003", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/packages/devtools-reps/src/object-inspector/components/ObjectInspector.css", "devtools/client/debugger/packages/devtools-reps/src/reps/reps.css", "devtools/client/shared/components/reps/reps.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3f85c8cde30cc0ac36c57242e9abd01e347066d7", "parents": ["54ff09f869d8e81bda1bf1c76816e8c6792ccf66"], "tags": []}, {"author": "diana.iacos \u003cdiana.iacos@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533365 - On tablets the icon from Sync page its not displayed correctly; r=petru a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31963", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/AboutPages.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/icons/preparation/AboutPagesPreparer.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "80259caee8e3b023f2c2a638c59f20334646679d", "parents": ["3f85c8cde30cc0ac36c57242e9abd01e347066d7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558709359, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "opoprus@mozilla.com"}, "11304": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging ddc0c7609e57ad43e1a28888ffffcbdf02131a53 with DEVEDITION_68_0b4_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8b6003b4680a925e9255f23b6f02da9ed5c2068e", "parents": ["80259caee8e3b023f2c2a638c59f20334646679d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release DONTBUILD", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d12a77191f9d0667d61edc9454f40d2d8e1b8bb1", "parents": ["8b6003b4680a925e9255f23b6f02da9ed5c2068e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558710818, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11305": {"changesets": [{"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 33e163907440 (bug 1551520) for causing build bustages. a=backout", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/clip_scroll_tree.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/display_list_flattener.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/picture.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/prim_store/mod.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e5a7fef8ed318119d84241732cf4c92c859f0e17", "parents": ["d12a77191f9d0667d61edc9454f40d2d8e1b8bb1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558710945, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "csabou@mozilla.com"}, "11306": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Manually bump the Fennec Beta version number. a=release", "files": ["mobile/android/config/version-files/beta/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c11a76e9f0e14effb5a7aec0063ba1b48ac32bb8", "parents": ["e5a7fef8ed318119d84241732cf4c92c859f0e17"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554249 - Publish Fennec nightlies to the beta track by default. r=jlorenzo, a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32502", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/push-apk/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "342f01df71a8421e39232da98d9e0f0c808a327c", "parents": ["c11a76e9f0e14effb5a7aec0063ba1b48ac32bb8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558717708, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11307": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrei Oprea \u003candrei.br92@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552768 - Remove hover style rules on Windows for the search input field. r=nhnt11 a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31772", "files": ["browser/themes/windows/syncedtabs/sidebar.css", "toolkit/themes/windows/global/textbox.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1d17556df566802d63e1239d7c42e44772c9a734", "parents": ["342f01df71a8421e39232da98d9e0f0c808a327c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552275 - Fix Copy Link context menu in DevTools Inspector markup view. r=gl a=jcristau\n\n- Fixes the references to the correct event handler & InspectorFront after a previous mass refactoring in Bug 1529364.\n- Augments a test to ensure the clipboard content is correct executing the context menu action to copy a link.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31765", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/markup/markup-context-menu.js", "devtools/client/inspector/markup/test/browser_markup_links_04.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "baf9be06329bcfa0777295b41b55b23debafb195", "parents": ["1d17556df566802d63e1239d7c42e44772c9a734"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jason Laster \u003cjlaster@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552609 - Adding a logpoint fails and breaks locations. r=davidwalsh a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31870", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/breakpoints/index.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/Editor/Breakpoint.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/Editor/ColumnBreakpoint.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/Editor/ConditionalPanel.js", "devtools/client/debugger/src/components/Editor/menus/breakpoints.js", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/.eslintrc", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/browser.ini", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/browser_dbg-breakpoints-cond-source-maps.js", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/browser_dbg-breakpoints-cond.js", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/helpers.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a5352b191e5a39803a6ed74a48279529277aa6e6", "parents": ["baf9be06329bcfa0777295b41b55b23debafb195"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552609 - Fix eslint failure. r=jlast a=jcristau", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/src/actions/breakpoints/index.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "daa553c05384776bc8c79f5ac4e5f3570d91a320", "parents": ["a5352b191e5a39803a6ed74a48279529277aa6e6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550771 - Deadlock in SharedMemoryBasic_mach triggered by AV1 playback r=jld a=jcristau\n\nDon't hold gMutex when calling HandleSharePortsMessage() from PortServerThread to avoid deadlock.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31694", "files": ["ipc/glue/SharedMemoryBasic_mach.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b40f41fc5bef54def5ea1d0ccc0727f142dfdbd", "parents": ["daa553c05384776bc8c79f5ac4e5f3570d91a320"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eugen Sawin \u003cesawin@me73.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489669 - [1.4] Add Storage Controller API. r=baku,snorp a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32153", "files": ["mobile/android/components/geckoview/GeckoViewStartup.js", "mobile/android/geckoview/api.txt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoRuntime.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/StorageController.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/doc-files/CHANGELOG.md", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewStorageController.jsm", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d6c54c50418ca7f3b4714a13a97455540e963785", "parents": ["3b40f41fc5bef54def5ea1d0ccc0727f142dfdbd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552354 - resolve video promise when we finish playing the last frame. r=jya a=jcristau\n\nWe should resolve video playing promise when we finish playing the last frame. Otherwise, it would cause playback to be ended earlier than its original duration.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32051", "files": ["dom/media/mediasink/VideoSink.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b7c117554a7ea876c00b404f0d5985cf2af67fd1", "parents": ["d6c54c50418ca7f3b4714a13a97455540e963785"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558722475, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "11308": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 1 - New background images for the release stub installer. r=agashlin a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31139", "files": ["browser/branding/official/bgstub.jpg", "browser/branding/official/bgstub_2x.jpg"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ade4160b638774fdc46bc31a4c000dd95ebba81", "parents": ["b7c117554a7ea876c00b404f0d5985cf2af67fd1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 2 - Fix GetTextWidthHeight for strings with no line breaks. r=agashlin a=jcristau\n\nThe current implementation of GetTextWidthHeight attempts to guess how much\nheight a string needs to fit into a given width based on how long the string\nis when rendered onto one line of unlimited width. This doesn't work because\nbreaking up the string into lines introduces additional space at the end of\nthe lines that the single-line method doesn't account for.\nThis patch replaces all of that logic with asking DrawText to render the\nstring into the width of interest and then just seeing how much height it\nended up needing in order to do that.\n\nWe also take the opportunity to clarify what GetDlgItemBottomDU was doing,\nbecause it isn't exactly what it claimed to be doing.\n\nDepends on D31139\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31140", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/installer/windows/nsis/common.nsh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8886e6d132f086ae69eeea8b0f96688d9591dba0", "parents": ["5ade4160b638774fdc46bc31a4c000dd95ebba81"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 3 - Add support for BrandProductName to SetBrandNameVars. r=agashlin a=jcristau\n\nBrandProductName is a recently-introduced branding string which is intended to\nnot change with the channel of the product; e.g., for a Nightly Firefox build,\nBrandShortName is not \"Firefox\", it's \"Nightly\", but BrandProductName is still\n\"Firefox\". Some of the new stub installer copy needs a name string like this.\n\nDepends on D31140\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31141", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/installer/windows/nsis/common.nsh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8f835eddb73d8f302b30efc97a4005fb43f5b31", "parents": ["8886e6d132f086ae69eeea8b0f96688d9591dba0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 4 - Add a macro for converting dialog units to screen pixels. r=agashlin a=jcristau\n\nWe typically want to define sizes of elements in the stub installer in terms of\ndialog units because those are independent of DPI. But sometimes we need to do\nsome calculations or invoke some API that needs pixels. So this function takes\na number of dialog units and an axis (because dialog units are not square) and\nconverts them to screen pixels using MapDialogRect.\n\nDepends on D31141\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31142", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/installer/windows/nsis/common.nsh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1fc004020e57440833c6f3a58a001cf4dde5dff", "parents": ["a8f835eddb73d8f302b30efc97a4005fb43f5b31"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 5 - Change the default installer UI font for en-US. r=agashlin a=jcristau\n\nSegoe UI Light couldn't accomodate the new stub installer visual design, and\nit already wasn't used for other languages (including other Englishes), so\nswap it out for regular weight Segoe UI.\n\nDepends on D31142\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31143", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/installer/windows/nsis/locale-fonts.nsh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "41b706ab3dac3cb1b2a640fbc29a2624caa1fa9c", "parents": ["b1fc004020e57440833c6f3a58a001cf4dde5dff"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 6 - Remove a couple of no longer needed stub installer strings. r=agashlin a=jcristau l10n=trailhead\n\nDepends on D31143\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31144", "files": ["browser/locales/en-US/installer/nsisstrings.properties"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4e75132ecb51125eb96f6439c59cbeb0ade93566", "parents": ["41b706ab3dac3cb1b2a640fbc29a2624caa1fa9c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 7 - Add and normalize stub installer UI parameters. r=agashlin a=jcristau\n\nThis patch adds a bunch of new defines for stub installer UI parameters that\nwere previously hard coded or implicit, moves several that were universal into\nthe branding files, removes several no longer used ones, and changes the names\nof some others to match a standard naming convention.\n\nDepends on D31144\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31145", "files": ["browser/branding/aurora/branding.nsi", "browser/branding/nightly/branding.nsi", "browser/branding/official/branding.nsi", "browser/branding/unofficial/branding.nsi", "browser/installer/windows/nsis/defines.nsi.in", "browser/installer/windows/nsis/stub.nsi"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8cd16438d96df1cbdb7c0340fd99b9e5b2659d5", "parents": ["4e75132ecb51125eb96f6439c59cbeb0ade93566"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548612 Part 8 - Implement the new stub installer UI design for release/beta. r=agashlin a=jcristau\n\nThis patch implements the new stub installer UI design for the official branding\nand leaves the other brandings mostly alone. Leaving them entirely alone was not\na goal because it wouldn't have been worth the hacks required, but the layouts\nand overall designs should be unchanged. The differences between the two designs\nare intended to be driven entirely by the branding files, so that the new design\ncan be easily expanded to the other channels once art assets exist.\n\nDepends on D31145\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31146", "files": ["browser/installer/windows/nsis/stub.nsi", "toolkit/mozapps/installer/windows/nsis/common.nsh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37268a8937c5afac3c47fbb0428d3d2f751e3891", "parents": ["a8cd16438d96df1cbdb7c0340fd99b9e5b2659d5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553400 - XMLHttpRequestDoneNotifier should own XHR, not vice-versa. r=baku a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32142", "files": ["dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "22734638bdcb7d90cdcce00aacaffad82cb8e3b7", "parents": ["37268a8937c5afac3c47fbb0428d3d2f751e3891"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511839 - Return the generated file if the camera result has \"inline-data\" action; r=VladBaicu a=jcristau\n\nHandle the case when Camera would actually save a new photo but would return\njust a thumbnail and not the full image\nhttps://github.com/aosp-mirror/platform_packages_apps_camera/blob/33c59af04ab44eff0e3806f140d472252300646a/src/com/android/camera/PhotoModule.java#L1345-L1371\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32307", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/FilePickerResultHandler.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5234a4220bae688d165edcd04567936f9d8ee823", "parents": ["22734638bdcb7d90cdcce00aacaffad82cb8e3b7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1543384 - Fix race in extension state setter r=kmag a=jcristau\n\nAs a side effect of this patch, the format of the \"state\" value of\n\"async shutdown timeout\" crash reports will change, as follows:\n\n\"Run manifest: \" has been replaced with \"Run manifest, \":\n\n```\n- Startup: Run manifest: asyncEmitManifestEntry(\"background\")\n+ Startup: Run manifest, asyncEmitManifestEntry(\"background\")\n```\n\nMultiple states are now separated by \", \" instead of \",\":\n\n```\n- Startup: Run manifest: manifest_name,manifest_version\n+ Startup: Run manifest, manifest_name, manifest_version\n```\n\n\"Run manifest\" will always have a \"Startup: \" in front of it:\n\n```\n- Startup: Emit Startup,Run manifest\n+ Startup: Emit Startup, Startup: Run manifest\n```\n\nAnd removed the `manifest_*` event dispatch since it has no listeners.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D26986", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/Extension.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa195c94dc1082186356e97094feb62e4e1f5b01", "parents": ["5234a4220bae688d165edcd04567936f9d8ee823"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dzmitry Malyshau \u003cdmalyshau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551520 - Use WR relative transform instead of the world inverse. r=gw a=jcristau\n\nSummary:\nThis is a follow-up to https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30600\n\nPreviously, I changed changed the space mapper logic to use the world transformations.\nThis was seemingly needed because we requrested the relation between primitives and\ntheir clip nodes, which could be in unrelated spatial sub-trees.\nHowever, I believe the change was a mistake, since for clips we should not even try\nto get the relative mapping, and clipping is done in world space for these cases.\nThis change reverts that logic back. Fingers crossed for the try to not show any\nasserts firing up inside get_relative_transform.\n\nTest Plan:\npending try\nhttps://treeherder.mozilla.org/#/jobs?repo=try&revision=dbd8fe9a797c680db0f64f02b019b2b4eaab4dd4\n\nReviewers: gw\n\nTags: #secure-revision\n\nBug #: 1551520\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32382", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/clip_scroll_tree.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/display_list_flattener.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/picture.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/prim_store/mod.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39c14a33468fde1a7316fc135243b647e750014f", "parents": ["fa195c94dc1082186356e97094feb62e4e1f5b01"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Varga \u003cjan.varga@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1540401 - Backout Part 2: Convert MOZ_DIAGNOSTIC_ASSERT back to MOZ_ASSERT since bug 1541775 hasn't been fixed yet; r=asuth a=jcristau l10n=trailhead", "files": ["dom/localstorage/ActorsParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "298f7d8bb0c03c97cb5254ca5fbe9835f3d8575b", "parents": ["39c14a33468fde1a7316fc135243b647e750014f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558726889, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "11309": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552627 - r=dveditz a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31722", "files": ["toolkit/components/prompts/src/SharedPromptUtils.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/handling/content/dialog.js", "toolkit/mozapps/handling/content/dialog.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dfc5b049c351cf99e7bddd88499d23c48659283b", "parents": ["298f7d8bb0c03c97cb5254ca5fbe9835f3d8575b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552627 - pt 2, r=dveditz a=jcristau\n\nDepends on D31722\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31723", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "27c8512c0e991930fa7bb01c6a89561772a64e48", "parents": ["dfc5b049c351cf99e7bddd88499d23c48659283b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551907 - Fix interaction between gray unmarking and weakmap marking r=sfink a=jcristau\n\nWe shouldn't allow a weak map to become gray after it has already been marked black.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31412", "files": ["js/src/gc/Marking.cpp", "js/src/gc/WeakMap-inl.h", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testGCGrayMarking.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "62a00a1d8a7b4726b6ecb424bc5e15533bb0d6cc", "parents": ["27c8512c0e991930fa7bb01c6a89561772a64e48"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1549812 - ScrollFrameRectIntoView should handle the frame going away. r=mats a=jcristau\n\nScrollToShowRect already considers that possibility, so not doing it on the\ncaller is a bug.\n\nIdeally scroll observers shouldn't be able to run script, more to that in a\nsecond.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31088", "files": ["layout/base/PresShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b08f23a595db9c6e00f3effd3cb329d8ca69780f", "parents": ["62a00a1d8a7b4726b6ecb424bc5e15533bb0d6cc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1558733930, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "11310": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging ddc0c7609e57ad43e1a28888ffffcbdf02131a53 with FIREFOX_68_0b4_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", 