spos subtrees. r=jwatt a=jcristau\n\nUgh, I accidentally introduced this in bug 1523071. :(\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33434", "files": ["layout/generic/nsAbsoluteContainingBlock.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "00203ea1541d75cb3d7d30096daa365682a1b7b9", "parents": ["836d74518ab6cda03a43f40b1824168875cd97d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555962 - Add a perf test which is an order of magnitude slower without the previous patch. r=heycam a=jcristau\n\nDepends on D33434\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33435", "files": ["testing/talos/talos/tests/perf-reftest-singletons/abspos-reflow-1.html", "testing/talos/talos/tests/perf-reftest-singletons/perf_reftest_singletons.manifest"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b3edc708cfc70665ca2bb6aea77749124e0e08ee", "parents": ["00203ea1541d75cb3d7d30096daa365682a1b7b9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556880 - Support GCC ARM preprocessor defines to detect the ARM target. r=chmanchester a=jcristau\n\nAlso set `fpu` to None for when we don't find it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33720", "files": ["build/moz.configure/arm.configure"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa3b94c7550a02cb7b9b23244cb62eb31af224e8", "parents": ["b3edc708cfc70665ca2bb6aea77749124e0e08ee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555530 - Don't use integrated assembler with clang on ppc64 and s390x. r=froydnj a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33728", "files": ["xpcom/reflect/xptcall/md/unix/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa64aae1b32d2f2a1cc1829c67da7e18c6899bd1", "parents": ["aa3b94c7550a02cb7b9b23244cb62eb31af224e8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ethan Glasser-Camp \u003cethan@betacantrips.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556391: Fix experiments that never expire r=mythmon a=jcristau\n\nAdd a test that simulates two Normandy \"runs\" to verify that the fix\nactually works.\n\nWhile we are here, fix a bug in the handling of\nuserFacingName/userFacingDescription.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33537", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/actions/PreferenceExperimentAction.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_actions_PreferenceExperimentAction.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "078657522e9e0c0db743a772efa0322d1e436057", "parents": ["aa64aae1b32d2f2a1cc1829c67da7e18c6899bd1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Omkar Konaraddi \u003cokonaraddi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1536816 - Remove the TODO comment in UrlbarInput::handleCommand. r=adw a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33694", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e6273336eca1ebbe8e810c04e887f08ada963bf9", "parents": ["078657522e9e0c0db743a772efa0322d1e436057"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Omkar Konaraddi \u003cokonaraddi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1534552 - Properly document selection resetting in UrlbarInput::_loadURL r=adw a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33713", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc39189ea1635cd833da6466ac5047d02d518117", "parents": ["e6273336eca1ebbe8e810c04e887f08ada963bf9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552687 - guard access to gfxDWriteFontFileStream with mutex. r=jfkthame a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32214", "files": ["gfx/2d/NativeFontResourceDWrite.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxDWriteCommon.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "44474b3668a5779c7f515a554c5de78341736592", "parents": ["fc39189ea1635cd833da6466ac5047d02d518117"], "tags": []}], "date": 1559748952, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "opoprus@mozilla.com"}, "11380": {"changesets": [{"author": "Anca Manu \u003canca.manu@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1371217 - Top Sites, Bookmarks & History are not centered; r=AndreiLazar a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D28833", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/home/TabMenuStrip.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d6fc2a5a92f24c730c2d033de7a3c692c2d01da0", "parents": ["44474b3668a5779c7f515a554c5de78341736592"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550051 - [Wayland] Don't track invisible popup windows, r=jhorak a=jcristau\n\nRecently we track and position all popups on Wayland which leads to\nwrong placement when parent popup window is hidden.\n\nIn this patch we use plain gtk_window_move() for hidden popups and\nwe don't track them so they can't be used as a parent window.\n\nAlso implement nsWindow::HideWaylandPopupAndAllChildren() to clearly\nhide a popup window with and its children windows.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31056", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1debce08ebc9f8f2b9ad5dacafe6bfd4d77df1e5", "parents": ["d6fc2a5a92f24c730c2d033de7a3c692c2d01da0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555866 - [Wayland] Don't position windows with zero height/width, r=jhorak a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: http