78 - Extend unicode::IsSpaceOrBOM2 to the full 32-bit range.  r=arai, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34189", "files": ["js/src/util/Unicode.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2a684be8b912e9b109f5ebf1389d248f04d0b922", "parents": ["9d4fbafe8fcd89685ad29790b7d69518ac0d8567"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nico Grunbaum \u003cna-g@nostrum.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553213 - Correct new MediaAccess telemetry probes. r=mjf, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32095", "files": ["dom/media/MediaDevices.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ca143ce6478199dca407a10754dc92a6970324b3", "parents": ["2a684be8b912e9b109f5ebf1389d248f04d0b922"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jason Orendorff \u003cjorendorff@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556136 - Fix misuse of readline() leading to a minor memory leak in the JS shell. r=jwalden, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33529", "files": ["js/src/shell/js.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "00a108b014dac0f3ee308bbc0a7cb097236ed79e", "parents": ["ca143ce6478199dca407a10754dc92a6970324b3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560345835, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11434": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julien Cristau \u003cjcristau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 2 changesets (bug 1547624) for causing crashes (bug 1348503). a=backout\n\nBacked out changeset e8341f537323 (bug 1547624)\nBacked out changeset e2f092d47d03 (bug 1547624)", "files": ["layout/painting/FrameLayerBuilder.cpp", "layout/painting/FrameLayerBuilder.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "34a9ba95e9085caa5dd46f7aa78b6a7c43897fcb", "parents": ["00a108b014dac0f3ee308bbc0a7cb097236ed79e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550911 - Show recommendations on extension and theme lists. r=robwu,flod,jaws l10n=flod a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30745", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "modules/libpref/init/all.js", "testing/profiles/common/user.js", "toolkit/locales/en-US/toolkit/about/aboutAddons.ftl", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.html", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_discover_view_clientid.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_list_view.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_list_view_recommendations.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "458469ed6f7e96118c0dd7224ce01f9f1a5f22bb", "parents": ["34a9ba95e9085caa5dd46f7aa78b6a7c43897fcb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557369 - Disable extension recommendations in discopane tests. r=mstriemer,zombie,mixedpuppy, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33979", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_discover_view.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_discover_view_clientid.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_discover_view_prefs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d04818deefaeb0263943fa8587d11d263b669b77", "parents": ["458469ed6f7e96118c0dd7224ce01f9f1a5f22bb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558194 - fix background styling for audit overlay in dark mode. r=mtigley, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34353", "files": ["devtools/client/accessibility/accessibility.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39fccba8099be5f91c88250aaa742b84c84e7985", "parents": ["d04818deefaeb0263943fa8587d11d263b669b77"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyura.zenevich@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558188 - ensure TreeView's tbody container does not get keyboard focus. r=mtigley, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34351", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/components/tree/TreeView.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c451276d2415e0ab637152d74e84ee1639e214de", "parents": ["39fccba8099be5f91c88250aaa742b84c84e7985"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557171 - Wrap the sys/cachectl.h system header on mips linux. r=froydnj, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33883", "files": ["config/system-headers.mozbuild"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e9e4c0ff22a9a2567a5baa738115d1eaabc15b4b", "parents": ["c451276d2415e0ab637152d74e84ee1639e214de"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557171 - Update vendored lmdb-rkv-sys to 0.8.4. r=chmanchester, a=jcristau\n\nThe only change is a fix for building for mips.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34096", "files": ["Cargo.lock", "third_party/rust/lmdb-rkv-sys/.cargo-checksum.json", "third_party/rust/lmdb-rkv-sys/Cargo.toml", "third_party/rust/lmdb-rkv-sys/lmdb/libraries/liblmdb/mdb.c", "third_party/rust/lmdb-rkv-sys/src/lib.rs", "toolkit/library/rust/shared/Cargo.toml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "065339c2d869fa75c5bbfb033f44a9d3effbd8ec", "parents": ["e9e4c0ff22a9a2567a5baa738115d1eaabc15b4b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dave Townsend \u003cdtownsend@oxymoronical.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555117: Ignore attempts to reset the profile when a new profile had to be created for the install. r=froydnj, a=jcristau\n\nSince bug 1518587 when a command line argument or environment variable requests\na profile refresh but no existing profile is selected we would just exit\nthinking that there is some problem here. But it turns out that the installer\nsometimes passes this argument when it doesn't know that the new install will\nnot use the existing profiles.\n\nSo instead we just ignore attempts to refresh when we create a new profile. To\ndo this we just have to remove the checks that bail out and continue to create\nthe new profile, nsAppRunner will see that a new profile has been created and\ncancel the attempted refresh anyway:\nhttps://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/ddb81c7a43ffada1f6cb4200c4f625e50e44dcf3/toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp#2021\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32891", "files": ["toolkit/profile/nsToolkitProfileService.cpp", "toolkit/profile/xpcshell/test_profile_reset.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7ba85dff0ee0d5bed92f83c2f2e3c97c86a2ce3", "parents": ["065339c2d869fa75c5bbfb033f44a9d3effbd8ec"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dave Townsend \u003cdtownsend@oxymoronical.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556173: Fix test_profile_reset.js on dev-edition builds. r=froydnj, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34002", "files": ["toolkit/profile/xpcshell/test_profile_reset.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55f38f0869b195d7f7e0cb3aff198d48e273129d", "parents": ["f7ba85dff0ee0d5bed92f83c2f2e3c97c86a2ce3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrei Teslovan \u003candrei.teslovan@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556382 - Reset error message for \"Find in page\" after dismiss; r=VladBaicu, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33934", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/FindInPageBar.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "881ef7c31cf0741e631f9da78e4c963e9809963e", "parents": ["55f38f0869b195d7f7e0cb3aff198d48e273129d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masatoshi Kimura \u003cVYV03354@nifty.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1549386 - Turn nsIPageThumbsStorageService.path into AString. r=Gijs, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33983", "files": ["toolkit/components/thumbnails/nsIPageThumbsStorageService.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2708dccfdc6ac5d499be81bdc605b5cd9d068437", "parents": ["881ef7c31cf0741e631f9da78e4c963e9809963e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560349226, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "jcristau@mozilla.com"}, "11435": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505330 - Only disable explicitly locked preferences. r=Gijs, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33505", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/connection.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser.ini", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_connection_bug1505330.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9053ab0103505c2813517e9d2ea9055f80be740", "parents": ["2708dccfdc6ac5d499be81bdc605b5cd9d068437"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557717 - Locked preferences shouldn't be reenabled. r=Gijs, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34163", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/connection.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "813ac8b3a652961ae7e235e188997957484b9703", "parents": ["b9053ab0103505c2813517e9d2ea9055f80be740"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556433 - disable shared buffer provider when using direct texture mapping. r=nical, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34242", "files": ["gfx/layers/PersistentBufferProvider.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "985afd2f291041c4e794f300ab3a22ed641166e9", "parents": ["813ac8b3a652961ae7e235e188997957484b9703"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Tung \u003cshes050117@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1546752 - Stop creating, writing, and reading the .metadata file in QuotaManager except the upgrades; r=janv, a=jcristau\n\nThe main goal of this issue is to reduce IO during the storage initialization\nand stop creating .metadata file since we already have .metadata-v2 file to\ntrack the information for the origin directory. Therefore, this patch only stop\ncreate, write, and read the .metadata file. And, leaving the work for removing\nit to the next minor upgrade.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D28824", "files": ["dom/quota/ActorsParent.cpp", "dom/quota/test/unit/test_basics.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55da5150365dc92235e56b3c9717f432abc68270", "parents": ["985afd2f291041c4e794f300ab3a22ed641166e9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551801 - Fix the velocity direction on pan gesture events. r=botond, a=jcristau\n\nThe gtest in this commit fails without the fix.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34245", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AsyncPanZoomController.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/test/gtest/InputUtils.h", "gfx/layers/apz/test/gtest/TestSnappingOnMomentum.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/test/gtest/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3af73765ec38e4b930a2868fbb765186fe3d359c", "parents": ["55da5150365dc92235e56b3c9717f432abc68270"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brian Hackett \u003cbhackett1024@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1545400 - Increment recursion depth when debugger has saved a thread's microtasks, r=arai,smaug, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32889", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/browser.ini", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/browser_dbg-idb-run-to-completion.js", "devtools/client/debugger/test/mochitest/examples/doc-idb-run-to-completion.html", "xpcom/base/CycleCollectedJSContext.cpp", "xpcom/base/CycleCollectedJSContext.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9870fe7e0c59c18edad254db9fa9da2428318800", "parents": ["3af73765ec38e4b930a2868fbb765186fe3d359c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525185 - Telemetry for HTML about:addons r=mixedpuppy,rpl, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31726", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.html", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_detail_view.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_discover_view.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_discover_view_clientid.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_list_view.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_list_view_recommendations.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_plugins.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_updates.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_interaction_telemetry.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d5aba1791f114e11166dec81517a7261a11b4859", "parents": ["9870fe7e0c59c18edad254db9fa9da2428318800"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557944 - Fix intermittent browser_html_plugins.js. r=rpl, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34616", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_plugins.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c39a1f9bcf7c48c91fc1bf6dddf84f9b23be2638", "parents": ["d5aba1791f114e11166dec81517a7261a11b4859"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1552180 - Poison Arena's zone pointer on free. r=sfink, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31494", "files": ["js/src/gc/Heap-inl.h", "js/src/gc/Heap.h", "js/src/jsutil.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "318ae93698afdf43aa73e5246de05ecbd1a3bbe4", "parents": ["c39a1f9bcf7c48c91fc1bf6dddf84f9b23be2638"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dave Townsend \u003cdtownsend@oxymoronical.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556832: Comparing compatibility versions goes on to check the build IDs when the version is newer. r=froydnj, a=jcristau\n\nWhen comparing compatibility versions we first compare the version part. If that\nshows us to be a downgrade then we stop checking at that point. But we must also\nstop checking if it shows us to be an upgrade since we don't need to check the\nbuild IDs at that point. This also applies to the check for the app build ID.\n\nThis means that a newer version with an older build id will appear to be a\ndowngrade.\n\nThis is problematic for safe mode because when safe mode runs it sets the\ncompatibility version to \"Safe Mode\" (bug 1556831) to ensure that caches are\ninvalidated on next startup. On the next run the Firefox version is considered\nas newer than \"Safe Mode\" so we would move on to comparing the build IDs. But\nthe Firefox build ID gets version compared to \"\" (since there isn't a build ID\npart in \"Safe Mode\"). Since build ID's are larger than 32-bit numbers we trigger\nbug 1556829 and the actual comparison depends on the value of the build ID\ntruncated to 32-bits. This seems to often be negative and so lower than the\napparent previous build ID causing us to think this is a downgrade.\n\nCue nfroydnj saying I told you so because if I'd written this as a more\ntraditional compare function as he suggested I probably would have caught this.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33702", "files": ["toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp", "toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.h", "toolkit/xre/test/gtest/TestCompatVersionCompare.cpp", "xpcom/base/nsVersionComparator.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "06b935ea69b8c02d7570ce8895071e75aa41a818", "parents": ["318ae93698afdf43aa73e5246de05ecbd1a3bbe4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560349568, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "jcristau@mozilla.com"}, "11436": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbn -\u003e 9fad9e0ab13c\ndsb -\u003e 7e115138cd71\ngn -\u003e 2daa4d3ce57c\nhsb -\u003e f554b31ed1b0\nis -\u003e 31c400e981ec\nit -\u003e e8bd6f75b90f\npt-BR -\u003e 2633c54ac003\nru -\u003e 4bcba0b023e0\nzh-TW -\u003e df427d165a74", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8ecfe2c0f5b1f51c6b117293501ff499b9043508", "parents": ["06b935ea69b8c02d7570ce8895071e75aa41a818"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbn -\u003e 9fad9e0ab13c\ndsb -\u003e 7e115138cd71\ngn -\u003e 2daa4d3ce57c\nhsb -\u003e f554b31ed1b0\nis -\u003e 31c400e981ec\nit -\u003e e8bd6f75b90f\npt-BR -\u003e 2633c54ac003\nru -\u003e 4bcba0b023e0\nzh-TW -\u003e df427d165a74", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5a9b1abe741ab5e5c2fe1a492887dd4558f1dc14", "parents": ["8ecfe2c0f5b1f51c6b117293501ff499b9043508"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560351633, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11437": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julien Cristau \u003cjcristau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551801 - fix build bustage.  a=bustage-fix\n\nAccount for bug 1546219 renaming mScrollSnapTypeY to mScrollSnapStrictnessY.", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/gtest/TestSnappingOnMomentum.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "54cc8fb1811067ecdfcf4cbf44b2da8c0b248601", "parents": ["5a9b1abe741ab5e5c2fe1a492887dd4558f1dc14"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560353784, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jcristau@mozilla.com"}, "11438": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kershaw Chang \u003ckershaw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556019 - Use int32 to store port number. r=valentin, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34123", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsIOService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a0fcf2ec279d7a5c2e72563bff25fef5f00786b1", "parents": ["54cc8fb1811067ecdfcf4cbf44b2da8c0b248601"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554158 - Always consume the enter key in UrlbarInput. r=mak, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34268", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarController.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55b21bb55d9eda98292b0af8931222f7ef0825f2", "parents": ["a0fcf2ec279d7a5c2e72563bff25fef5f00786b1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Agi Sferro \u003cagi@sferro.dev\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1554260 - Send WebExtension Page messages to GeckoSession. r=snorp, a=jcristau\n\nWebExtension pages introduce a case that was previously not possible: a script\nwith full WebExtension privileges that runs on a page with a GeckoSession\nassociated to it.\n\nThis breaks the assumption that all messages from a privileged context don't\nhave a GeckoSession associated to it. We fix this by checking if we can find an\neventDispatcher for the given window.\n\nThis also fixes the test which had the same wrong assumption.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D32512", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/WebExtensionTest.kt", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/WebExtensionEventDispatcher.java", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewWebExtension.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aac6fce419affdab022c4877a0690976d975d71a", "parents": ["55b21bb55d9eda98292b0af8931222f7ef0825f2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556774 - Don't handle Tab key when Ctrl or Alt are pressed. r=Gijs, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34269", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarController.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3d31a0e1b47e48c382364a560c65fe44fee0954a", "parents": ["aac6fce419affdab022c4877a0690976d975d71a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix enterprise policy test failures when HTML about:addons is enabled by default. r=mkaply,rpl, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31776", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser_policy_disable_flash_plugin.js", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser_policy_extensions.js", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "633c7ce9740c8f428812052468b8ecaae12b9a14", "parents": ["3d31a0e1b47e48c382364a560c65fe44fee0954a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Run browser_CTP_plugins.js on both XUL and HTML about:addons page. r=aswan,rpl, a=test-only\n\nDepends on D31776\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31777", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_CTP_plugins.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83af41aaeb7df6bfd934b335676e14a9bf191634", "parents": ["633c7ce9740c8f428812052468b8ecaae12b9a14"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix browser_gmpProvider and run tests on XUL and HTML about:addons. r=mossop, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31778", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_gmpProvider.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "32caceae9cac46abf47f1f19ec5ce00a228aba99", "parents": ["83af41aaeb7df6bfd934b335676e14a9bf191634"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix failures when browser_update_checkForUpdate run with HTML about:addons enabled. r=aswan, a=test-only\n\nDepends on D31778\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31779", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/webextensions/browser_update_checkForUpdates.js", "browser/base/content/test/webextensions/browser_update_findUpdates.js", "browser/base/content/test/webextensions/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "607906b633a7be3e2919ceba7c4c0d8ca3c007c7", "parents": ["32caceae9cac46abf47f1f19ec5ce00a228aba99"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix browser_dragdrop.js and fold browser_dragdrop_incompat into it. r=kmag, a=test-only\n\nDepends on D31779\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31780", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_dragdrop.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_dragdrop_incompat.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0cc06358290da5c2b93e6407e7eeb6d4ff49b1d6", "parents": ["607906b633a7be3e2919ceba7c4c0d8ca3c007c7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Rename browser_bug562797 to browser_history_navigation and run on XUL and HTML about:addons. r=kmag,rpl, a=test-only\n\nDepends on D31780\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31782", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug562797.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_history_navigation.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/discovery/api_response_empty.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fd69d7d0f0d080ffe71b6539b95103c106a28fb0", "parents": ["0cc06358290da5c2b93e6407e7eeb6d4ff49b1d6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Disable HTML about:addons on legacy XUL about:addons tests. r=kmag,rpl, a=test-only\n\nDepends on  D31782\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31789", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug562890.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug562899.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug562992.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug580298.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug587970.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug590347.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug591663.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug618502.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_details.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_discovery.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_discovery_clientid.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_globalwarnings.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_langpack_signing.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_legacy.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_legacy_pre57.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_list.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_manualupdates.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_plugin_enabled_state_locked.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_pluginprefs.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_sorting.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_sorting_plugins.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_tabsettings.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_theme_previews.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_types.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_uninstalling.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9688b1081c1db3d73d08418b2e78508ec7778d03", "parents": ["fd69d7d0f0d080ffe71b6539b95103c106a28fb0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix test failures with inline options in HTML about:addons. r=kmag, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34078", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_optionsPage_modals.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_optionsPage_popups.js", "browser/components/extensions/test/browser/head.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionPolicyService.cpp", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_options_ui.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_inlinesettings_browser.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webext_options.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webext_options_addon_reload.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "09a47b7d1716348806063aa220db1bf8b50b096c", "parents": ["9688b1081c1db3d73d08418b2e78508ec7778d03"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix tests when abuse reporting is enabled by default. r=rpl, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34174", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_detail_view.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_list_view.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9dbc53624d7c680cfa9c7d295b225e500dba0288", "parents": ["09a47b7d1716348806063aa220db1bf8b50b096c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix browser_webext_icon.js when HTML about:addons is enabled by default. r=rpl, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34183", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webext_icon.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "33f0e94f70414d47ba1f8c0a032fd5d4f20580a0", "parents": ["9dbc53624d7c680cfa9c7d295b225e500dba0288"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix browser_ext_browserAction_contextMenu.js when HTML about:addons is enabled. r=rpl, a=test-only\n\nWhen HTML `about:addons` is enabled, the \"Manage extension\" button still\nopens the add-on's details page, but without automatically loading the\ninline options.\n\nThe test assumed that it did and failed. This patch switches to a\ndifferent way of detecting that the menu item works as expected.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34209", "files": ["browser/components/extensions/test/browser/browser_ext_browserAction_contextMenu.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3bbbdeca9f13b3c20c6df3419c1726de429fb9e8", "parents": ["33f0e94f70414d47ba1f8c0a032fd5d4f20580a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Hide add-on preferences when not allowed in private windows, fix browser_webext_incognito.js. r=rpl, a=jcristau\n\nFix browser_webext_incognito.js to work with both XUL and HTML about:addons.\n\nThis patch also ensures that (inline) options UI is only shown in HTML\nabout:addons in private windows if add-ons are allowed access to it.\nbrowser_webext_incognito.js serves as a unit test for this.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34277", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_webext_incognito.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "82e6701f5dbbead6f5c610020fce9b3d62b8ab65", "parents": ["3bbbdeca9f13b3c20c6df3419c1726de429fb9e8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Fix browser_reinstall.js with HTML about:addons. r=robwu, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D31496", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_reinstall.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_updateid.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "466fe0fc7db3f5d4d740ff388c15aa7dc9eff14b", "parents": ["82e6701f5dbbead6f5c610020fce9b3d62b8ab65"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1551490 - Update test expectation of browser_reinstall.js for 68. r=rpl, a=test-only\n\nThe output of a non-existing attribute changed in bug 1552714.\nIn 69, the expectation is `{id: null, args: null}`.\nIn 68 and before, the expectation is `{id: \"\"}`.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34615", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_reinstall.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a2fc7a9510bdc4d1f18cae3f1938a79c9a8e0c67", "parents": ["466fe0fc7db3f5d4d740ff388c15aa7dc9eff14b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560360860, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "jcristau@mozilla.com"}, "11439": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1539019 - Disallow simulated OOM testing of worker threads because it's not thread safe r=jandem a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34328", "files": ["js/src/builtin/TestingFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit-test/tests/gc/bug-1530643.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8620e798567200858369c6508014d18d80793e3c", "parents": ["a2fc7a9510bdc4d1f18cae3f1938a79c9a8e0c67"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335085 - [marionette] Make use of \"WebDriver:NewWindow\" in firefox-puppeteer. r=webdriver-reviewers,ato a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33689", "files": ["testing/firefox-ui/tests/puppeteer/test_windows.py", "testing/marionette/puppeteer/firefox/firefox_puppeteer/ui/windows.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dde54edc86e14de2aa37d6d15b5a935ebcd77999", "parents": ["8620e798567200858369c6508014d18d80793e3c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335085 - [marionette] Fix \"WebDriver:SwitchToWindow\" for tab and window focus switching. r=webdriver-reviewers,ato a=test-only\n\nSelecting a different tab is asynchronous, and as such Marionette has\nto wait for the \"TabSelect\" event to be emitted. Further the chrome\nwindow also needs to be focused.\n\nDepends on D33689\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33690", "files": ["testing/marionette/browser.js", "testing/marionette/driver.js", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_switch_window_content.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1e1c5ad53cfc6456978165e9ccc6088c52fe678e", "parents": ["dde54edc86e14de2aa37d6d15b5a935ebcd77999"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335085 - [marionette] Simplify focus handling for window classes in firefox-puppeteer. r=webdriver-reviewers,ato a=test-only\n\nDepends on D33690\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33691", "files": ["testing/marionette/puppeteer/firefox/firefox_puppeteer/ui/windows.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "992cbc55ecf76c0117ea0ca081a53ec7178f019e", "parents": ["1e1c5ad53cfc6456978165e9ccc6088c52fe678e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557336 - Unset LC_CTYPE when executing pipenv. r=chmanchester a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34484", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/virtualenv.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "73460fd9b68d7ddd5266cda0d0693ec4b15de14c", "parents": ["992cbc55ecf76c0117ea0ca081a53ec7178f019e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560381006, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "apavel@mozilla.com"}, "11440": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 969c5587c144\nes-ES -\u003e b7dbfe7158ab\nfi -\u003e 8eed8dd7ebcf\nit -\u003e 590c679c67ce\nlo -\u003e e47bfb1b797f\nnl -\u003e 7a6ab93cf424\npl -\u003e 68fd5d7bc1a0\npt-BR -\u003e e49f4e3b9088\nro -\u003e ed48720759d2\nvi -\u003e a04cfa2018a0", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0570584cae2a1dabadf9fba89d08d492a7199f62", "parents": ["73460fd9b68d7ddd5266cda0d0693ec4b15de14c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 969c5587c144\nes-ES -\u003e b7dbfe7158ab\nfi -\u003e 8eed8dd7ebcf\nit -\u003e 590c679c67ce\nnl -\u003e 7a6ab93cf424\npl -\u003e 68fd5d7bc1a0\npt-BR -\u003e e49f4e3b9088\nro -\u003e ed48720759d2\nvi -\u003e a04cfa2018a0", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa07e1e87d3b98a8187590f3840954f8b90cdf0e", "parents": ["0570584cae2a1dabadf9fba89d08d492a7199f62"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560427228, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11441": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558763 - [marionette] Disable \"browser.tabs.remote.separatePrivilegedContentProcess\" by default. r=maja_zf a=test-only\n\nDue to bug 1557457 it can happen that loading a web page with eg.\na HTTP auth prompt, no modal dialog will be shown by Firefox. As\nsuch disable this preference for now globally, until all the issues\nwith privileged content processes have been solved.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34710", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/geckoinstance.py", "testing/marionette/components/marionette.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8b7e99e3f6cf77e4e95112833841f708677dad1", "parents": ["fa07e1e87d3b98a8187590f3840954f8b90cdf0e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504201 - [marionette] Re-enable test TestScreenCaptureChrome.test_formats. r=webdriver-reviewers,ato a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33780", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_screenshot.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b4a6eae77dcef08cbfafb77adb86360f01347006", "parents": ["a8b7e99e3f6cf77e4e95112833841f708677dad1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555012 - Enable HTML about:addons by default r=rpl a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34337", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e5f23ab4c98d50b3fedbeff19e9e88f1bd2e5193", "parents": ["b4a6eae77dcef08cbfafb77adb86360f01347006"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555012 - Enable abuse reporting at about:addons by default r=rpl a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34530", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f9cc16a870b5ae16f88139e069c8ec609b18f44", "parents": ["e5f23ab4c98d50b3fedbeff19e9e88f1bd2e5193"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1555012 - Skip about:addons in browser_aboutURLs.js r=rpl a=jcristau\n\nUpon enabling the HTML about:addons discovery pane, about:addons page\nstart to send a fetch request from the default user context, instead of\na content load request with the tab's user context.\n\nThis mismatch in userContextId triggers the following debug assertion:\nhttps://searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/c606cdd6d014f/netwerk/base/nsNetUtil.cpp#3021-3024\n\nThis assertion can be ignored, because the request has no credentials,\nso its context should not matter.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34688", "files": ["browser/components/contextualidentity/test/browser/browser_aboutURLs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa39f1f84dbd753fb836bd12063f744912ef5351", "parents": ["0f9cc16a870b5ae16f88139e069c8ec609b18f44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luca Greco \u003clgreco@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1556389 - Show report action only on currently supported addon types. r=mstriemer a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34341", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/abuse-report-frame.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_abuse_report.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f2fce0eb3d26339f6f40aae062b66202765c2d68", "parents": ["fa39f1f84dbd753fb836bd12063f744912ef5351"], "tags": []}, {"author": "sotaro \u003csotaro.ikeda.g@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1553969 - Do not disable WebRender at ImageBridgeChild when gecko uses WebRender r=nical a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33753", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c6f045553e3ed87b7aa1e83aeef576da9f52f361", "parents": ["f2fce0eb3d26339f6f40aae062b66202765c2d68"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kenny Levinsen \u003ckl@kl.wtf\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1548499 - Set EGL context before call to eglSwapInterval. r=sotaro a=jcristau\n\nThe EGL context must be set before the call to eglSwapInterval to ensure that it will operate on the correct context.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D30282", "files": ["gfx/webrender_bindings/RenderCompositorEGL.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f1e0fc04cdc9b79a97037f61cf09ea170e3325c", "parents": ["c6f045553e3ed87b7aa1e83aeef576da9f52f361"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557324 - Fix JSTerm keyboard navigation in old input. r=Honza. a=jcristau\n\nHitting Ctrl+ArrowRight didn't have any effect on windows/linux.\nThe patch fixes this and add a test to make sure a user can\nnavigate from word to word using Ctrl (or Alt on OSX) and\nArrow Left/Right keys.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34312", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/components/JSTerm.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser_jsterm_autocomplete_arrow_keys.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0c663b927b277a56270923e22fb22911b8f5ada5", "parents": ["1f1e0fc04cdc9b79a97037f61cf09ea170e3325c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557996 - Make `HTMLEditor::GetSelectedElement()` not treat an element as selected when it's followed by a \u003cbr\u003e element r=m_kato a=jcristau\n\nCurrently, `HTMLEditor::GetSelectedElement()` is not used in mozilla-central\nand mainly used for handling double clicks in the editor with its complicated\npath.  In most cases, users don't want double clicks to cause showing\nproperty dialog in mail composer.  Therefore, we must be able to stricter in\nthe complicated path.\n\nThis patch adds new check whether the selected range ends immediately before\na `\u003cbr\u003e` element.  If it's end at a `\u003cbr\u003e` element, we shouldn't treat found\nelement as selected.\n\nNote that when `\u003ca href=\"...\"\u003e` element is double-clicked, the element itself\nis selected like `\u003cimg\u003e` element.  So, we don't need to worry about the case\nwhich is that users probably want to update a link with double-clicking since\nsuch case is handled by the first optimized path in the method.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34335", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditor.cpp", "editor/libeditor/tests/test_nsIHTMLEditor_getSelectedElement.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9d6ef6164ec1cdc79d1420def6f40ad28d5bd7eb", "parents": ["0c663b927b277a56270923e22fb22911b8f5ada5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Hammond \u003cmhammond@skippinet.com.au\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550967 - ensure sync's username pref is set whenever FxA has a user. r=tcsc a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34309", "files": ["services/fxaccounts/FxAccounts.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7222059b69403e52b9b35e045ad0d9aa3afbd581", "parents": ["9d6ef6164ec1cdc79d1420def6f40ad28d5bd7eb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560433141, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "opoprus@mozilla.com"}, "11442": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34867", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json", "services/settings/dumps/security-state/intermediates.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bea9c810099f78f3a5867d7e9bd5e7a7f4477bf3", "parents": ["7222059b69403e52b9b35e045ad0d9aa3afbd581"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Klotz \u003caklotz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1549797: Remove loader hooks for TestDllBlocklist from mozglue; r=mhowell, a=jcristau\n\nWe remove the debugging hooks that were added to check to see whether a DLL\nwas loaded, as we can just as easily check that by querying the loader itself.\nPlus, we shouldn't be exporting a bunch of test-only loader hooks from mozglue\nin our release builds, which is what we are currently doing.\n\nWe also remove Injector, InjectorDLL, and TestDLLEject, as these tests can\njust as easily be done from within TestDllBlocklist by creating a thread with\nLoadLibrary* as the entry point. The CreateRemoteThread stuff, while a more\naccurate simulation, has no material effect on whether or not the thread\nblocking code works.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34444", "files": ["mozglue/build/WindowsDllBlocklist.cpp", "mozglue/build/WindowsDllBlocklist.h", "mozglue/tests/gtest/Injector/Injector.cpp", "mozglue/tests/gtest/Injector/moz.build", "mozglue/tests/gtest/InjectorDLL/InjectorDLL.cpp", "mozglue/tests/gtest/InjectorDLL/moz.build", "mozglue/tests/gtest/TestDLLBlocklist.cpp", "mozglue/tests/gtest/TestDLLEject.cpp", "mozglue/tests/gtest/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4ff3f4af050df6110825067eef38240126c2274a", "parents": ["bea9c810099f78f3a5867d7e9bd5e7a7f4477bf3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557790 - fix initialization of blocklist clients, r=aswan, a=jcristau\n\nIn order for the remote settings blocklist to sync, we need to ensure that\nthe corresponding remote settings clients are created (see also\nhttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1557790#c2 ). This is\nnecessary because the blocklist clients are not in the `main` bucket.\n\nThis would otherwise happen as soon as any consumer asked the blocklist\nfor any block data, but that's not going to happen unless the list of\nadd-ons or plugins changes. Even if there are no changes to the local\nlists of installed things, we do need blocklist updates because\notherwise already-installed items would never get blocked even if/when\nthey are added to the blocklist.\n\nThe client initialization should have no other side effects (in terms of\nperformance/cost) beyond ensuring they get included in things we ask for\nwhen the update-timer fires.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34550", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/plugins/head.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/Blocklist.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/AddonTestUtils.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/rs-blocklist/test_blocklist_clients.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/rs-blocklist/test_blocklist_targetapp_filter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f8429b9c6790161fa215e5d340ba05eae544c6de", "parents": ["4ff3f4af050df6110825067eef38240126c2274a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aaron Klotz \u003caklotz@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558561: Fix missing population of RTL_OSVERSIONINFOW::dwOSVersionInfoSize; r=mhowell, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34559", "files": ["browser/app/winlauncher/DllBlocklistWin.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "807e9d8f83dc8b87a5e1c76061f63fac179010d0", "parents": ["f8429b9c6790161fa215e5d340ba05eae544c6de"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560434212, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11443": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558628 - Add back nsIDocShell.hasTrackingContentBlocked since it is used in the webcompat report-site-issue extension; r=baku a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34613", "files": ["browser/extensions/report-site-issue/test/browser/browser_report_site_issue.js", "docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "docshell/base/nsIDocShell.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f82fe365272472c28fb2c988ce6124bdec1fd7c", "parents": ["807e9d8f83dc8b87a5e1c76061f63fac179010d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1544950 - Part 1: Add-on warning messages for HTML about:addons r=rpl a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34449", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.html", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddons.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/aboutaddonsCommon.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/message-bar.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug590347.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_html_warning_messages.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_langpack_signing.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "591c4abc2dd073781bb75c61b05df3e9fc572350", "parents": ["1f82fe365272472c28fb2c988ce6124bdec1fd7c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1544950 - Part 2: Global add-on warnings for HTML about:addons r=rpl a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34452", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.xul", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_globalwarnings.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_gmpProvider.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_history_navigation.js", "toolkit/themes/shared/extensions/extensions.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7a85d0459d6d449791e31f6d4ee1e108bab183a6", "parents": ["591c4abc2dd073781bb75c61b05df3e9fc572350"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558499 - DownloadDirectory policy should prevent selecting \"ask every time\" r=jaws a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34585", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser_policy_downloads.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "545958c08c72b81767cd8460ce82d4d130dfbbbb", "parents": ["7a85d0459d6d449791e31f6d4ee1e108bab183a6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1558546, ensure range element has a frame before starting drag operation, r=hsivonen a=jcristau\n\nThis should be the minimal patch to fix the issue (should be safe for branches too).\n\nReusing an existing mouse/touch test for the crash testing.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34717", "files": ["dom/html/HTMLInputElement.cpp", "dom/html/test/forms/test_input_range_mouse_and_touch_events.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "44d7135f115d5ca4d150424b2b425841d2db4139", "parents": ["545958c08c72b81767cd8460ce82d4d130dfbbbb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1557555 - Quantumbar: Autofill only when text is entered, never when it's removed (e.g., on backspace). r=mak a=jcristau\n\nAutofill only when the user enters text -- i.e., when event.data in _on_input is non-empty. That allows us to simplify autofill quite a bit. We can get rid of the edit action listener that we previously used to detect selection deletion, and we also don't need the prefix check (lastSearchStartsWithNewSearch).\n\nTherefore this fixes both this bug (bug 1557555) and bug 1545731/719888.\n\nThis makes one other change: We can check event.inputType in _on_input to tell whether the user is pasting, rather than keeping a _valueIsPasted property that we set in _on_paste.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34645", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/UrlbarTestUtils.jsm", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_UrlbarInput_unit.js", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_autoFill_backspaced.js", "browser/components/urlbar/tests/browser/browser_autoFill_undo.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c434d19d03d5461e54fa22dfb82eaed4cd6631b", "parents": ["44d7135f115d5ca4d150424b2b425841d2db4139"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_68_0b10_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_68_0b10_RELEASE", "FENNEC_68_0b10_BUILD1", "FENNEC_68_0b10_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_68_0b10_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_68_0b10_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1560435128, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "opoprus@mozilla.com"}, "11444": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 4c434d19d03d5461e54fa22dfb82eaed4cd6631b with FIREFOX_68_0b10_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a0ea982feff9d2b2ade29bc2bd0f698eca1ff3e1", "parents": ["4c434d19d03d5461e54fa22dfb82eaed4cd6631b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560446925, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11445": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 4c434d19d03d5461e54fa22dfb82eaed4cd6631b with DEVEDITION_68_0b10_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8393a4dc4dad3468218095cb8f17f3eacea7cea4", "parents": ["a0ea982feff9d2b2ade29bc2bd0f698eca1ff3e1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560447795, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "11446": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 4c434d19d03d5461e54fa22dfb82eaed4cd6631b with FENNEC_68_0b10_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e2af396f76076920acb9807e199f695ff28e99c8", "parents": ["4c434d19d03d5461e54fa22dfb82eaed4cd6631b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge esr68 to beta. a=merge", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "3a6ccd26874306b6d9cf9c3c32290fa98dbf247d", "parents": ["8393a4dc4dad3468218095cb8f17f3eacea7cea4", "e2af396f76076920acb9807e199f695ff28e99c8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550291 - Add new \"Crash handler\" notification channel; r=JanH, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33028", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/notifications/NotificationHelper.java", "mobile/android/base/locales/en-US/android_strings.dtd", "mobile/android/base/strings.xml.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a74afc1a7a210a327a623a075c5c206ef08e60ed", "parents": ["3a6ccd26874306b6d9cf9c3c32290fa98dbf247d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550291 - Android Q: Use the overlay permission or a foreground notification to start the crash handler; r=VladBaicu, a=RyanVM\n\nAndroid Q doesn't allow starting Activities from background.\nhttps://developer.android.com/preview/privacy/background-activity-starts\n\nWe can either piggy-back the SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW permission given by the user\nfor the Tab Queue functionality or use a foreground notification from where\nusers could start `CrashReporterActivity`.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D33029", "files": ["mobile/android/app/src/main/res/values/ids.xml", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/CrashHandlerService.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/CrashReporterActivity.java", "mobile/android/base/locales/en-US/android_strings.dtd", "mobile/android/base/strings.xml.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "22cfa63e856377c0b7f502d194d4b17dc0c3acc9", "parents": ["a74afc1a7a210a327a623a075c5c206ef08e60ed"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1550291 - Ensure we save CRASHED status to be able to restore previous tabs; r=AndreiLazar, a=RyanVM, l10n=flod\n\nDefault app behavior for when a crash occurs involves starting an Activity that\nlets users submit a crash report and maybe provide additional info.\nIn the event of a crash we want to restore for the user all previous tabs, this\nActivity being the component that saves the CRASHED status that will trigger\nthe restore process.\n\nOn Android Q, when a crash notification is posted but ignored by the user, upon\nstarting the app would not know it crashed and it would not try restoring tabs.\nExecuting the \"save CRASHED status\" logic whenever a crash occurs, irrespective\nof if we'll show the Activity or just post a notification ensures users will\nalways have their previous tabs restored.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D34826", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/CrashHandlerService.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/CrashReporterActivity.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9ac627048305775d78799ea022d269d18d593262", "parents": ["22cfa63e856377c0b7f502d194d4b17dc0c3acc9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1560461563, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "11447": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\neo -\u003e 7da4ce932c6f\nes-CL -\u003e ab40c79bec85\net -\u003e b2ed039679b6\neu -\u003e d967eaaab1e0\nfr -\u003e fa0f455baeb1\nid -\u003e b5920a695c4c\nnl -\u003e c1cbc1be5f37\npt-PT -\u003e 3aa7fe565d3b\nro -\u003e 4b47bc8639fc\nsk -\u003e 559104ff218f\nsl -\u003e 9b27dfe830b6\nuk -\u003e dd8cd4f1d9d0", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "abf322efc723897624040ad5e48519845b821bd1", "parents": ["9ac627048305775d78799ea022d269d18d593262"], "tags": 